      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;One thing that disgusts me is the stigma associated with an unepic'd cleric.&amp;nbsp; I was glad to finally get my 1.0 at level 62, but I never had a guild to help with it.&amp;nbsp; I solo'd most of it, and I made pickup raids for the rest.&amp;nbsp; You always get funny looks because you don't have your epic.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Now, I'm suffering the same stigma because I don't have my shield yet.&amp;nbsp; I've already farmed all the drops I can (lacking only the brain from WW because I need to kill Mirot first) for 1.5 and even the first stage of 2.0.&amp;nbsp; I saw a thread on here saying how any group can expect a cleric in RSS to have their click shield, but why?&amp;nbsp; Is it so easy for clerics to get great guilds that help them?&amp;nbsp; There aren't many middle-ground guilds anymore, they're either low end or high end, so where does a self-sufficient cleric fit into all this?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I never joined a raid guild until I was level 70.&amp;nbsp; Not once.&amp;nbsp; I got all my PoP flags purely from pickup raids.&amp;nbsp; I got an 8k mana pool from OoW and DoN content ONLY... NO RAIDS.&amp;nbsp; Finally joined a raid guild, and now there's this huge stigma because I have no 1.5.&amp;nbsp; And, of course, they don't want to help with my epic because I'm a lowly app, but it makes me feel like I may not get accepted because I don't have my epic, so it's a catch-22 for me.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I've earned everything I have myself, I never had anything handed to me.&amp;nbsp; Not gear, not spells, not flags, nothing.&amp;nbsp; I got everything I have from my own sweat and tears.&amp;nbsp; So why do I have such a hard time getting by?&amp;nbsp; Why do people still talk crap?&amp;nbsp; What do these people know about someone that started the game a year ago and that hasn't been privileged with a lengthy history in a certain guild or on a certain server?&amp;nbsp; Epic 1.0 was so easy to do, but 1.5 isn't so easy to just grab pickup raids for.&amp;nbsp; I really think guilds should rethink the way they treat clerics without click shields.&amp;nbsp; Just because you're new, and don't have all the bells and whistles, doesn't mean you aren't great at your class.&amp;nbsp; I have a friends list full of people that come to me first if they need a cleric for a group, why?&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Because they know I'm good.&amp;nbsp; New to the game DOES NOT MEAN NEWBIE.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Anyway... rant's over.&amp;nbsp; Not sure what my point was, but I saw a thread on this forum that basically said, "any group in RS can expect their cleric to have their click shield", like it's so %^&amp;amp;*ing easy?&amp;nbsp; And this guy was a class rep.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;What do you know?&amp;nbsp; You've probably been playing since the game came out and never had to worry from day one about having a guild that'll dish everything out to you.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
